HEADWORD: Succotash
<hw>Suc"co*tash</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Narragansett
Indian <ets>m'sickquatash</ets> corn boiled whole.]</ety> <def>Green
maize and beans boiled together. The dish is borrowed from the native
Indians.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>suckatash</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Succoteague</ent>⟦br⟧
